  "prompt": "Are there any TV series similar to How to Get Away with Murder?",
  "response": "Yes, there are several TV series that share similar themes, tones, or storytelling styles with **How to Get Away with Murder**. Here are some recommendations:\n\n1. **Scandal** - Created by Shonda Rhimes, this political thriller follows Olivia Pope, a crisis management expert, as she navigates high-stakes scandals and personal drama.\n\n2. **Grey's Anatomy** - Another Shonda Rhimes creation, this medical drama features intertwining personal and professional lives of doctors in a hospital, with plenty of twists and emotional moments.\n\n3. **The Good Wife** - This legal and political drama follows Alicia Florrick as she returns to work as a lawyer after her husband\u2019s scandal. It combines courtroom drama with personal and political intrigue.\n\n4. **Suits** - A legal drama focused on a talented college dropout who lands a job at a prestigious law firm despite never having attended law school. The series explores legal cases and personal relationships.\n\n5. **The Killing** - A crime drama that delves into the investigation of a murder case, exploring the impact on the detectives and the victim's family, with a dark and suspenseful tone.\n\n6. **Mindhunter** - This psychological thriller follows FBI agents as they interview serial killers to understand their psychology, blending crime-solving with intense character studies.\n\n7. **Damien** - This psychological horror series follows a young man who discovers his ties to the Antichrist, exploring themes of morality and supernatural elements.\n\n8. **The Night Of** - An anthology series that follows a complex murder case and explores the criminal justice system, revealing the intertwining lives affected by the crime.\n\n9. **Big Little Lies** - A drama that revolves around a group of mothers in a wealthy California community, exploring dark secrets, lies, and a murder mystery that unfolds throughout the series.\n\n10. **The Good Fight** - A spin-off of The Good Wife, this series follows a lawyer who starts over after losing her savings due to a financial scam, dealing with political and social issues in a contemporary setting.\n\nThese series often feature strong character development, intricate plots, and a blend of legal or moral dilemmas that fans of **How to Get Away with Murder** may enjoy.",
